From: OctaneOS <octaneos@local>
Date: Sat, 12 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] typec: husb311: send PD hard reset on shutdown unconditionally

husb311_shutdown() previously skipped the PD hard reset when
chip->battery_exist was false.  On the Cubie A7S (no battery), usb_psy
is NULL so husb311_init_tcpci_data_late() returns before setting
battery_exist, leaving it false.  The hard reset was therefore never
sent during warm reboot.

Without a hard reset, the monitor receives no signal to cleanly exit
DP Alt Mode.  The HUSB311 chip stays powered through the SoC reset
(it has its own I2C supply), so CC lines stay valid but the DP main
link dies when the EDP PHY is reset.  The monitor enters a half-exited
state with HPD de-asserted.  Combined with the phy_switcher deadlock
fixed in patch 0008, this means the display stays dark on every warm
reboot.

Fix: remove the battery_exist guard in husb311_shutdown().  During an
orderly reboot (warm or cold) the SoC remains powered, the I2C bus is
up, and the TCPC_TRANSMIT write succeeds.  If it fails (late shutdown
path with bus already clocked down), the error is logged and silently
ignored -- this is already the behaviour for a failed write.

Signed-off-by: OctaneOS <octaneos@local>
---
 bsp/drivers/power/typec/tcpci_husb311.c | 5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/bsp/drivers/power/typec/tcpci_husb311.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/power/typec/tcpci_husb311.c
@@ -832,9 +832,8 @@
 	disable_irq(chip->gpio_int_n_irq);
-	if (!chip->battery_exist) {
-		dev_dbg(chip->dev, "no battery, hardreset forbidden");
-		return;
-	}
+	/* Send hard reset unconditionally: on warm reboot the SoC stays powered
+	 * so the I2C write is safe.  This tells the monitor to cleanly exit
+	 * DP Alt Mode and cycle HPD, ensuring it re-detects the source when
+	 * the new kernel re-establishes Alt Mode. */
